1. Enable Docker Remote API
   Modify /etc/default/docker file to include parameter `-H tcp://0.0.0.0:4243`
   - `DOCKER_OPTS="-H tcp://0.0.0.0:4243"`
     
2. Hack
 - docker.host entry in /etc/hosts

3. Enable basic security 
Manage Jenkins > Setup Security >
Security Realm
  Select:
    - "Enable Security"
    - "Jenkinsâ€™ own user database" -> De-select "Allow users to sign up"
  Authorization:
    - "Logged-in users can do anything"
  Save
  Sign up form should show up
 Once logged in select user at top right > Configure > Show API Token...
 to see ... token
